The paper presents a novel motion planning algorithm using neural networks, which is highly relevant to the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of neural networks for motion planning also falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves encoding workspaces from point cloud measurements, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the efficiency and generalization of the proposed method, which are topics of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
